  <!-- Title -->
  <h1 style="color:#933a35; font-size:28px; font-weight:700; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:2px; margin-bottom:32px; text-align:center;">
    Privacy Policy
  </h1>

  <div style="color:#6B6B6B; font-size:15px; line-height:1.7;">

    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Last Updated:</strong> May 2, 2026
    </p>

    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      Your privacy matters to us. This policy explains how Tich Labs GmbH ("we," "us," "our") collect, use, store, and protect your personal data under GDPR (EU Regulation 2016/679) and other applicable privacy laws.
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:#933a35; font-size:17px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:10px;">1. Data Controller</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Tich Labs GmbH</strong><br>
      Email: <a href="mailto:info@season.vision" style="color:#933a35;">info@season.vision</a><br>
      For Data Protection Inquiries: <a href="mailto:privacy@season.vision" style="color:#933a35;">privacy@season.vision</a>
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:#933a35; font-size:17px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:10px;">2. What We Collect</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Account Information:</strong> Email, name, language preference, authentication data
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Health Data (Special Category, Article 9):</strong> Cycle dates, symptom logs (mood, energy, sleep, pain, physical symptoms, cravings, mental state, discharge, sexual intercourse), temperature, weight, and personal notes. <strong>Processing this data requires your explicit consent.</strong>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Calendar & Reminder Data:</strong> Events, appointments, reminders, and superpower logs (engagement tracking)
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Usage Data:</strong> Browser type, IP address (anonymized), pages visited, time spent (for analytics and service improvement only)
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:#933a35; font-size:17px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:10px;">3. Consent & Legal Basis</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Health Data Processing (Article 9(2)(a)):</strong> We process health data only with your explicit, informed consent. You can manage your consent at any time in Settings → Data & Privacy. You can withdraw consent at any time; we will stop processing and may delete historical data per your retention choices.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Other Data Processing:</strong> Legitimate interest (service provision), contract performance (you created an account), and legal obligations.
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:#933a35; font-size:17px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:10px;">4. How We Use Your Data</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      • Provide and improve the Season app<br>
      • Send reminders (email only, no SMS/push)<br>
      • Respond to support inquiries<br>
      • Analyze app usage and fix bugs<br>
      • Comply with legal obligations
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or share your data with third parties for marketing.
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:#933a35; font-size:17px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:10px;">5. Data Retention</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Cycle & Symptom Data:</strong> Retained for 3 years from last update (allows historical trend analysis). After 3 years, automatically deleted unless you withdraw consent earlier.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Calendar Events & Reminders:</strong> Retained for 1 year from creation date, then deleted.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Account Data:</strong> Retained while your account is active. Deleted within 30 days of account deletion.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Consent Records & Audit Trail:</strong> Retained for 3 years for legal compliance (GDPR Article 7).
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:#933a35; font-size:17px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:10px;">6. Your GDPR Rights</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      You have the right to:
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      • <strong>Access (Article 15):</strong> Request a copy of your data. Use Settings → Account → Download Data or email <a href="mailto:privacy@season.vision" style="color:#933a35;">privacy@season.vision</a>.<br>
      • <strong>Portability (Article 20):</strong> Export all your data as JSON from Settings → Account → Download Data.<br>
      • <strong>Rectification (Article 16):</strong> Correct inaccurate data in Settings.<br>
      • <strong>Erasure (Article 17):</strong> Delete your account and all data. Go to Settings → Account → Delete Account. Data is permanently erased within 30 days.<br>
      • <strong>Withdraw Consent (Article 7(3)):</strong> Stop health data processing at any time in Settings → Data & Privacy. Previous processing is not retroactively unlawful.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      To exercise any right, email <a href="mailto:privacy@season.vision" style="color:#933a35;">privacy@season.vision</a> with proof of identity. We'll respond within 30 days (extendable to 90 days for complex requests).
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:#933a35; font-size:17px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:10px;">7. Data Storage & Security</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      • Data stored on <strong>Render.com</strong> (US-based, GDPR-compliant via Standard Contractual Clauses)<br>
      • PostgreSQL database with encryption at rest<br>
      • HTTPS/TLS for all connections<br>
      • Access logs retained for 1 year<br>
      • No backups shared with third parties
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:#933a35; font-size:17px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:10px;">8. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>OAuth Providers (Google, Apple, Facebook):</strong> Used for sign-in only. Their privacy policies apply. We do not store OAuth tokens.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Email Service (Resend):</strong> Reminder emails sent via <a href="https://resend.com" style="color:#933a35;">Resend</a>. GDPR-compliant Data Processing Agreement in place.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Error Tracking (Sentry):</strong> Technical errors logged. Sentry has signed a Data Processing Agreement (DPA) under GDPR.
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:#933a35; font-size:17px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:10px;">9. International Transfers</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      Your data may be processed in the US (Render.com servers). We rely on <strong>Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs)</strong> approved by the European Commission to ensure GDPR-compliant transfers. Your fundamental rights are protected by the same standards as processing in the EU.
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:#933a35; font-size:17px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:10px;">10. Contact & Complaint</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Questions?</strong> Email <a href="mailto:privacy@season.vision" style="color:#933a35;">privacy@season.vision</a>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <strong>Complaint:</strong> If you believe we've violated your privacy rights, you have the right to lodge a complaint with your national data protection authority (e.g., <a href="https://www.bfdi.bund.de" style="color:#933a35;">BfDI</a> in Germany).
    </p>

